snippet: Prime Minister David Cameron played down the vote by lawmakers in London on a resolution criticizing his handling of the crisis over whether Britain should leave the European Union.
abstract: Britain's Prime Min David Cameron plays down vote by lawmakers in Parliament on resolution criticizing his handling of crisis over whether Britain should leave European Union.

byline.original: By STEPHEN CASTLE and ALAN COWELL
byline.contributor: Stephen Castle reported from London, and Alan Cowell from Paris.

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister David Cameron played down the vote by lawmakers in London on a resolution criticizing his handling of the crisis over whether Britain should leave the European Union.

headline.seo: Cameron Survives Europe Vote by Closer Margin Than Forecast
headline.main: Cameron Survives Challenge on Europe Policies, but Vote Is Closer Than Expected
headline.print_headline: Cameron Survives Challenge on Europe Policies, but Vote Is Closer Than Expected
